==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plaintiff
<hw>Plain"tiff</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>plaintif</ets> making complaint, plaintive; in Old French equiv. to
<ets>plaignant</ets> complainant, prosecutor, fr. <ets>plaindre</ets>.
See <er>Plaint</er>, and cf. <er>Plaintive</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>One who commences a personal action or suit to obtain a remedy for
an injury to his rights; -- opposed to <ant>defendant</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

